Class FactBaseFromList

All Implemented Interfaces:
org.nlogo.api.Primitive, org.nlogo.api.Reporter, scala.ScalaObject
public class FactBaseFromList
extends org.nlogo.api.DefaultReporter

This class implements the "from-list" primitive for the factbase extension. From-list takes a list of facts, including a list of field names as the first entry, as input and creates a new fact base from it. To call this primitive from NetLogo, use factbase:from-list list-of-field-names-and-facts

Author:
Ruth Meyer

public java.lang.Object report(org.nlogo.api.Argument[] args,
                               org.nlogo.api.Context context)
                        throws org.nlogo.api.ExtensionException,
                               org.nlogo.api.LogoException
Creates a new fact base from the given list and reports it. The first argument args[0] has to contain the list of field names as its first entry.

Parameters:
args - the arguments to this call of from-list
context - the NetLogo context
Returns:
a reference to the newly created fact base
